article_title: Willy Street Co-op opts for a less intimidating 'Eat Local Month'
article_text:
Madison, WI (53711)

Today

Thunderstorms in the morning, then skies turning partly cloudy late. High near 85F. Winds SSW at 5 to 10 mph. Chance of rain 80%..

Tonight

Some clouds and possibly an isolated thunderstorm after midnight. Low 63F. Winds light and variable. Chance of rain 30%.

article_metadata.description: Even locavores found the Eat Local Challenge either too difficult or redundant, so this year the co-op is scaling back with a smaller series of weeklong challenges.
article_metadata.author: Lindsay Christians | The Capital Times
